  <hyper:location>
    <hyper:title>XSLT Trap: CORS doesn't work for XSLT transformations</hyper:title>
    <hyper:description xlink:label="here">
      <h:section>
        <h:p>Another oldy but goody: CORS doesn't work for XSLT transformations in Chrome. This means that it's impossible to refer to an XSL stylesheet stored on a remote server even if CORS has been set up. This is a big problem for local hyperspaces... we'll need to think of a solution as part of <h:a href="solution-asset-management.xml">asset management</h:a>.</h:p>
        
        <h:p>There is no workaround for this -- you could perhaps hack something up with Javascript but you probably have better to do. Your best bet is to go and <h:a href="https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=101152">add another star to the bug report</h:a>.</h:p>
      </h:section>
    </hyper:description>
    
    <hyper:resource
      xlink:href="https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=101152"
      xlink:title="cross-site xml to xslt security block"
      xlink:label="cross-site-xslt-block" />
    <hyper:link xlink:from="here" xlink:to="cross-site-xslt-block" />
    
